    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hey BLA :)\n\nHow do you handle the i18n on your side? Is that:\n- Only defined through the browser locale and not changeable?\n- A dropdown in the UI that changes the displayed language of the UI (but still use the same results from Algolia)\n- A dropdown in the UI that change the index/filters of the results to target those of a specific language?\n\nDepending on the use case there are several ways to do that, but most of them will involve defining a function as the template. If you define a function, it will be called on each render and you can then dynamically chose which error message to display.\n",
    "created_at": "2016-05-25T23:15:46Z",
