    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Yes, if you define your own function it completly bypass the Mustache/Hogan template compilation and you have to build the resulting string yourself.\n\nThat being said, if you are using ES6, you easily replicate the same behavior with the backtick and `${}` syntax of string interpolation.\n",
