  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "True! You can use them in a function.\n\nBut they can't be used as values. They are very much hardcoded inside the function that use them. You can't do:\n\n``` js\nvar myTemplate = `bar ${foo}`;\n// already translated as a string using the context\n\nvar myRenderedTemplate = fn(`baz ${bar}`);\n// Translated to string before the function call\n```\n",
